directions: In a large mixing bowl combine all the dry ingredients.
In a separate medium-sized bowl, whisk together the apple sauce, olive oil, milk, banana, and honey.
Add the wet ingredients to the dry ingredients and stir to combine.
Fill lightly greased muffin cups, and bake for 15-20 minutes, or until the tops have browned. The insides will be exceptionally moist!
Let the muffins cool to firm up, or eat them while they are ultra-tender and warm!
title: Whole-Wheat Zucchini Muffins
